ory of exploration, and all of the technology and trades necessary to craft a globe.</p><p>These images and sidebars are lovely, but also what you might expect from the cover. What I could not anticipate was the book‚Äôs narrative text. And that is what delighted me most.</p><p>From my distant vantage in California, Bellerby &amp; Co. is an elegant English establishment. Their globes sell to Harrod‚Äôs extravagantly wealthy shoppers. They were endorsed by the Queen, twice! Today, two-dozen artisans produce 600 globes a year under the Bellerby cartouche. Their studio photographs look like they were orchestrated by a Dutch Master. But it wasn‚Äôt always so. </p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5bd6ed3c-4292-4db3-8bd0-6770ce216c81_1065x1332.jpeg" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/V-WE_AK3ktbe1awHNIzV_ 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/D- 848w, https://reader.miniflux. 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/_xOvawWaHKGZG4kovs4HUX_ 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux." alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/_ 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/i6gt9JSzUap25ESNqU7ObZ3vrpwSMFxw6BxvjLEt-_U=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd184NDgsY19saW1pdCxmX2F1dG8scV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkY1YmQ2ZWQzYy00MjkyLTRkYjMtOGJkMC02NzcwY2UyMTZjODFfMTA2NXgxMzMyLmpwZWc= 848w, https://reader.miniflux. 1272w, https://reader.miniflux. 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"/></picture></a><figcaption>Photo by Euan Myles, <a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/Ck_GjWgsM5o/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">posted</a> Nov 2022</figcaption></figure><p>The book‚Äôs narrative reveals an adventure you cannot find on Instagram.</p><p>The story is mostly about Peter Bellerby, mostly by himself, mostly failing as he tries to make his first globes in the wake of the 2008 financial crisis. Chucking carloads of imperfect plaster hemispheres into the dump. Transforming homegrown maps. Wet gores tearing because they were printed against the grain. Mismatched watercolors. Tacky varnish. Foundry alloys that rudely expand and contract with the damp environment. Scrounging for antique wood stock. One-of-a-kind suppliers that go out of business.</p><p>It is a years-long journey that no sane person would rationally endure: madness. It happened in a home kitchen, cold warehouses, and stacks of industrial stock. Favorite possessions were sold to keep the pursuit alive. The journey had dozens of easy exits, reasons to compromise or quit altogether. Yet, Bellerby persisted. What kind of person completes this kind of journey?</p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F133f93f1-e815-49f6-a3c0-9aa09c1b2ff5_612x612.jpeg" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux. 424w, https://reader.miniflux. 848w, https://reader.miniflux. 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/eA74gyQwOqZ2TTEkOxaz4VYhznu9bmjgrroNYDVU-aU=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xNDU2LGNfbGltaXQsZl93ZWJwLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGMTMzZjkzZjEtZTgxNS00OWY2LWEzYzAtOWFhMDljMWIyZmY1XzYxMng2MTIuanBlZw== 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/tyLl6eTWqrFtcbN8ikvN-" width="612" height="612" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/NLV_ 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/BZFKV0iK9QrXQwfxnDLTIFJHvtj6ePExuOG_4fUQ1bI=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd184NDgsY19saW1pdCxmX2F1dG8scV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkYxMzNmOTNmMS1lODE1LTQ5ZjYtYTNjMC05YWEwOWMxYjJmZjVfNjEyeDYxMi5qcGVn 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/-vJJtGHfFNWI_ 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/tyLl6eTWqrFtcbN8ikvN- 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"/></picture></a><figcaption><a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/dbzyy-BOsf/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">posted</a> August 2013</figcaption></figure><p>Today, Bellerby exudes refined elegance, you might even call it posh. It is certainly proper.</p><p>Look beyond this surface and you might glimpse the magic: Today, it‚Äôs not natural or obvious to create a proper globe. To do so you have to have to be a stubborn maverick. I detect a defiant rebel pulsing inside. And maybe that‚Äôs the special blend: one part posh and one part punk.</p><p>Bellerby‚Äôs unwavering dedication to his vision‚Äîhis mad determination‚Äîis evident in his rationale for hand-engraving their brass meridian rings:</p><blockquote><p>Finding a hand-engraver took several years. Indeed, it seems this may well be an existential point in time for this important craft. Many of the jewellery shops in Hatton Garden and in the West End used to have engravers on their staff; nowadays almost all engraving is done by machine. . . . for me, a handmade globe absolutely needs a hand-engraved meridian.</p></blockquote><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd1128297-0db3-423c-bb18-82a5eca23d24_1080x977.jpeg" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/FgXpI0Dsfb29odVguU8XlU3- 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/OggbQ_ 848w, https://reader.miniflux. 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/_q2stSau--V5jnC6Q- 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/F84bgd8YVIccN41dXO4-" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/9Tc1EczNtyaxxjfR2- 424w, https://reader.miniflux. 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/yXYtdLhE-_oH8V-1_8C0TZimR_7RQp9e0hRxqat7A-M=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xMjcyLGNfbGltaXQsZl9hdXRvLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGZDExMjgyOTctMGRiMy00MjNjLWJiMTgtODJhNWVjYTIzZDI0XzEwODB4OTc3LmpwZWc= 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/F84bgd8YVIccN41dXO4- 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"/></picture></a><figcaption>Photo by Toby Essex</figcaption></figure><p>Every day that Bellerby flailed, he learned more, eventually assembling the talents and formulations necessary to create a handmade globe.</p><p>Informationally, reading <em>The Globemakers</em> steps you through Bellerby‚Äôs journey of discovery. It educates you along the way in how to make a globe, neatly loading you with appreciation for the work that goes into each of their beautiful works of art. (My inner-engineer salivated at all of the custom machine work.) The book also divulges the marketing talents of Jade, who can be credited for bringing the world‚Äôs attention to Peter‚Äôs globes. By the book‚Äôs end you will consider adding your deposit to their months-long waiting list.</p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F03d52c08-7caf-4f88-a05e-2fdd8433e86d_1280x853.jpeg" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/GOM_02Kon7HICn7gY_ 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/qK5oscZWo0xMJofzbTQ6WzKLtHehOS8gl1_5yuULoWo=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd184NDgsY19saW1pdCxmX3dlYnAscV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkYwM2Q1MmMwOC03Y2FmLTRmODgtYTA1ZS0yZmRkODQzM2U4NmRfMTI4MHg4NTMuanBlZw== 848w, https://reader.miniflux. 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/IMgdAnOjXWT_RcsaprqzrluWy9r_ 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/wY7dyBt-" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/i4dZnpnMLoBPA3cHfwZxd3s_ 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/a-uI2WOIDnU1m_ 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/5sQxpf-LM-Vq4waWt7GW-5RStpBJ7KQeIyDXj_Vf4NI=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xMjcyLGNfbGltaXQsZl9hdXRvLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGMDNkNTJjMDgtN2NhZi00Zjg4LWEwNWUtMmZkZDg0MzNlODZkXzEyODB4ODUzLmpwZWc= 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/wY7dyBt- 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"/></picture></a></figure><p>Emotionally, my read had an even more surprising effect on me. It resonated with the same feeling that begins Charlie Chaplin‚Äôs call for technological humanism. ‚ÄúWe have developed speed, but have shut ourselves in. Machinery that gives abundance has left us in want. . . . We think too much, and feel too little.‚Äù</p><p>Bellerby‚Äôs globes prove that our knowledge and understanding can be beautiful, delightful, and enriching. In fact, this is how it used to be: art and science strode hand-in-hand.  In contrast, the starkness of today&#39;s digital age invokes the outbursts of Charlton Heston. ‚ÄúYou maniacs. You blew it up. Damn you! Damn you all to hell!‚Äù</p><p>Bellerby‚Äôs achievement shows not only that tools and objects of information can be glorious, it suggests that perhaps they should be.</p><blockquote><p>There is something quite magical in spinning a globe . . . the truth is, it still gives me a thrill. . . . Without exception, all visitors to the studio treat every globe like a delicate object, first requesting permission to touch it before asking, ‚ÄòMay I spin it?‚Äô The look of delight on their faces when they do so, very gently, is one of the greatest perks of my job. At that point, it often feels a connection is formed.</p></blockquote><p>Thanks to Peter Bellerby, an extinct art is reborn. Reading <em>The Globemakers </em>left me yearning for a world with more treasures that evoke the same sense of wonder as his globes.</p><p><em>Onward!‚ÄîRJ</em></p><p><em>Chartography</em> is supported by readers like you. Become a paid subscriber today.</p><h1>About</h1><p>Data storyteller RJ Andrews helps organizations solve high-stakes problems by using visual metaphors and information graphics: charts, diagrams, and maps. His passion is studying the history of information graphics to discover design insights. See more at¬†<a href="http://infowetrust.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">infoWeTrust.com</a>.</p><p>RJ‚Äôs recently published series, <a href="https://visionarypress.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Information Graphic Visionaries</a>, a new book series celebrating three spectacular data visualization creators. With new writing, complete visual catalogs, and discoveries never seen by the public. His first book <em>Info We Trust, How to Inspire the World with Data</em>‚Äîwill be published in a remastered edition in 2024.</p>